<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-376-766  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 376 766.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computers in Healthcare  July 1989 v10 n7 p51(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Anytime, anywhere, healthcare. (Bryan Memorial Hospital computernetwork system) (column)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Martin, Larry.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Bryan Memorial Hospital, a 344-bed tertiary care hospital inLincoln, NE, has designed and installed a computer system, aphysicians' office interface (POI) networking product that allowsaccess to patient information from almost anywhere or anytime,including some doctors' homes.andP;  The system was made easy to use bysuch features as menu pathways and function combinations to speedusers through the program.andP;  System security is through acode-callback-password procedure.andP;  Users can access information onpatient data, patient location, medical and admitting information,record summaries, medication profiles, ancillary orders, neworders and lab or radiology results.andP;  Security measures continueeven when the user uses the system.andP;  Bryan covers the expense ofadding a physician to POI because the hospital considers POI abenefit to admitting physicians.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Local Area NetworksMedical RecordsSystem DevelopmentData SecurityNebraskaLincoln, Nebraska.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>